{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:02.392Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Enhancing Interactive Visualization**\n\nI'm now thinking we can replace the standard `div` elements with `WorkspaceCard` components! The stats cards will get a premium mouse-spotlight glow, which is a significant improvement. I'm also considering integrating a custom interactive SVG visual to showcase a zero-trust secure tunnel between the Client and GFF Systems triage, adding a **Sovereign Network Architecture / Gateway Node Topology Graphic**. This visual will replace the \"Initialize Support Wire\" form with a bento or tabbed layout for initialization and tunnel information when no ticket is selected.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:04.558Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Visualizing Cryptographic Flow**\n\nI'm now diving into the implementation details of the interactive SVG. I envision an animated diagram depicting cryptographic signals flowing within the \"Sovereign Tunnel Gateway\". The interactive nodes will display mock real-time credentials and status, specifically for the Client Gateway Node, GFF Deep Shield, and Cores System Tria-Bot. I'm focusing on crafting a visually compelling and informative representation of the secure tunnel. I'm now referencing the existing code of `app/portal/support/page.tsx` around the ticket form to prepare.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:06.284Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Tabbed Interface**\n\nI'm now implementing a tabbed interface to replace the \"Initialize Support Wire\" form when no ticket is selected. I will have \"Intake Form\" and \"Secure Gateway Topology\" tabs. The \"Secure Gateway Topology\" tab will feature an interactive SVG diagram. I'm excited about this, as it will replace the static form with a more engaging visual representation of the zero-trust tunnel.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:08.024Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Premium Visuals**\n\nI'm now focusing on elevating the visual design to a premium level. I'm thinking of incorporating custom SVG nodes with pulsing indicators, dynamic connection cables, and animated data packets using CSS keyframes. I am excited to provide a dynamic metadata panel that updates with user interactions. I'm exploring the design assets needed for this SVG, aiming for a fully CSS and SVG-based solution for performance. I have just realized that I may need to update the dynamic subpage too. I am checking the navigation from the primary support page, too.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:10.046Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Navigation Patterns**\n\nI'm now investigating the navigation flow within `app/portal/support/page.tsx`. I've realized that selecting a ticket sets `selectedTicketId` via the Master-Detail pattern. On desktop, this triggers a split-screen. I'm currently looking at how this behaves on small screens, focusing on the conditional rendering of the list and detail sections.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:13.452Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Optimizing Mobile UX**\n\nI'm now focusing on improving the mobile experience, especially the layout and navigation. I'm noting that the list and detail sections currently stack on mobile, potentially creating a cluttered experience. I'm focusing on the back arrow's functionality. I think it makes sense to hide the ticket list when a ticket is selected on mobile.\n\n\\n\\n\n\n**Streamlining Mobile Display**\n\nI'm now thinking about how to hide the ticket list on mobile after selection. I'm examining how to implement conditional rendering based on screen size, likely using a state variable to control the list's visibility when a ticket is selected. Currently I see that a back arrow already exists, that when clicked will set the `selectedTicketId` to `null`. This will likely require updating the classnames based on the value of a new `isListVisible` variable. I'll need to assess the existing classNames.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:14.680Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Mobile Layout**\n\nI'm now refining the mobile layout for the support page to improve the user experience. I've realized that the current setup stacks both the ticket list and the detail section on mobile, leading to a cluttered display. I've found a way to implement conditional rendering using `hidden` and `block` classes, improving navigation and creating an excellent mobile chat interface. I'm now examining the overall design for areas of improvement.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:16.524Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Enhancing Card Styles**\n\nI'm now integrating `WorkspaceCard` components and thinking about how to refine the visual style. I'm focusing on adding custom icons, elegant descriptions, and glowing accents to each card for a premium look. I'm also planning to enhance the existing filters block by wrapping it within a `WorkspaceCard` to provide a cleaner visual presentation. Finally, I'm thinking about integrating a premium tab bar within the right panel.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:18.674Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Visualizing Premium Chat**\n\nI'm now focusing on the right panel's chat UI. I am thinking of enhancing the chat with a premium, dark-mode design. I'm planning to add immersive messages, live typing indicators, and better bubble designs for both client and support replies. I'm also thinking of creating a security header. I'll include the telemetry trace display, too. I'll need to focus on a futuristic aesthetic that emphasizes security and engagement.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:20.315Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Diagnostic Accordions**\n\nI'm now planning to enhance the left column with \"Quick Diagnostic Protocols\" using interactive accordions. These will provide instant solutions for architectural issues. Each accordion will include protocols like \"Rotating HSM Seals,\" \"SGX Page Cache Re-Allocation,\" and \"NIST Compliance Audit Trail,\" with smooth disclosure animations and custom hover highlights. I'm focusing on making the support page more intuitive.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:22.770Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Preserving Ticket State**\n\nI'm now focusing on preserving the existing state management and local storage functionality within the support page. I've re-examined the code, confirming that the `gff_support_tickets` data is saved and fetched using `localStorage`. I must ensure that any changes I make to state variables or data structures maintain compatibility with this existing mechanism, as it is crucial for the page's functionality. I am now double-checking the code to confirm.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:23.794Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Simplifying Imports**\n\nI've just found a simpler way to import `WorkspaceCard`, directly from `@/components/private-app`. I've updated the imports in `app/portal/support/page.tsx` and it's cleaner than before. This streamlined method removes unnecessary complexity, which is great! I'm moving on to consider the implementation of premium-looking components.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:26.047Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Integrating Card-Based Layout**\n\nI'm now integrating `WorkspaceCard` components and replacing the existing `div` wrappers. I'm focusing on the stat cards, and plan to add icons like `MessageSquare`, `Clock`, `Shield`, and `FileText`. I am thinking that these will each have custom pulses to indicate status. I'm excited about this high-fidelity design!\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:27.875Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Tabbed Interface**\n\nI'm now designing the tabbed interface at the top. I'm using \"intake\" and \"topology\" states to render either the intake form with a \"Securing Handshake...\" transition or a live SVG topology diagram. The topology will show three interactive nodes: Client Node, Sovereign Shield, and Tria-Bot, for an amazing UI. I am very excited about all the animations.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:29.681Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Interactive Nodes**\n\nI'm now making each SVG node hoverable and clickable! Upon interaction, a metadata panel will appear, displaying Node Name, Connection Status, Network Latency, Active Cryptography Protocol, and Attestation Seal Signature. I'm excited about adding animated SVG lines with flowing particles to visualize cryptographic signals using CSS animations and `stroke-dashoffset`.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:32.089Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Diagnostic Actions**\n\nI'm now adding interactive elements to the accordion items in the diagnostic section! Each will include an \"Initiate Local Telemetry Reset\" or \"Test Attestation Handshake\" button. Clicking the buttons will trigger a simulated diagnostics process with a terminal-like console log, providing impressive interactivity. The simulated diagnostic process will show: `[OK] LOCAL REPLICATION STATE READ SUCCESSFUL (MEMCACHE: SECURE)`, `[OK] SGX EPC ENCLAVE INTEGRITY CONFIRMED`, and `[OK] RE-ATTESTATION SIGNATURE: 0x8FDE...3FAA (VALID)`.\n\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:38:34.751Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Visualizing Ticket Priority**\n\nI'm now implementing visual indicators for SLA status within the `WorkspaceCard`. I plan to use a red glow for Critical (P1), amber for High (P2), and blue for Medium (P3) tickets. I am excited to display these levels!\n\n**Styling Chat Bubbles**\n\nI'm now focusing on styling the chat bubbles, enhancing the user experience. I'm styling client bubbles with a dark gradient and deep-blue border. I'm giving admin/operator bubbles an emerald border with a soft green glow. I'm adding professional avatars for operator replies.\n\n**Integrating Telemetry Panel**\n\nI am now implementing the \"Systems Engineers Telemetry Panel\" inside the chat. I'll add a collapsible \"SECURE ENCLAVE LOGS\" section with simulated JSON payloads. I'm excited about including simulated telemetry data!\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
