{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:42:04.169Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining The Approach**\n\nOkay, I've got a plan to refine the original simpler versions in lines 77 to 158. Now, I'm focusing on replacing `handleCreate` and integrating `runDiagnostic` within `/app/portal/support/page.tsx`. Currently, I'm working on crafting these replacements.\n\n\n**Integrating Ticket Creation**\n\nI'm now integrating the ticket creation logic. I am focusing on replacing the `handleCreate` function entirely with an updated function I'm calling `createTicket`. The goal is to streamline the ticket creation process, including initializing a new ticket with a unique ID and managing the related state updates effectively.\n\n\n**Implementing Reply Updates**\n\nI'm now focused on implementing the reply updates. I've got the `preventDefault` call, and the handling for empty text or a missing ticket ID. Currently, I'm working through the logic to add the client reply to the specific ticket, update the ticket's status if resolved, and save the changes. I'm also addressing the bot reply, though currently, the reply is hardcoded.\n\n\n**Verifying Cryptographic State**\n\nI'm verifying the cryptographic state, and analyzing the CPU and HSM logs. The key rotational interlocks are functioning as expected, and propagation latency is negligible. I'm confirming that the cryptographic state is re-asserted.\n\n\n**Refining Submission Handling**\n\nI'm now refining the ticket submission handling. I've got the basic structure for the new ticket creation using `handleCreate`, which includes generating a unique ID and managing the related form state updates. I'm focusing on the state transition upon submission and validating the form inputs to ensure that the ticket's data are valid. I'm currently working to replace the original function with an updated function I'm calling `handleCreate`.\n\n\n**Updating Ticket Management**\n\nI'm now integrating the updated `handleCreate` function with refinements to how new tickets are saved and displayed. Specifically, I've implemented a sequence that generates a unique ID, saves the new ticket, and clears the form's state. I'm focusing on the state transition upon submission and validating the form inputs. I've also added a confirmation toast to the user.\n\n\n**Implementing Bot Replies**\n\nI am now implementing the bot replies. I've updated the logic to dynamically generate bot replies based on the ticket category. I've successfully added logic to update the ticket data and implemented different messages for various categories, such as AI Operations, Billing, Governance, and others. The ticket status will also be updated appropriately, and the messages reflect the nature of the operations for each ticket.\n\n\n**Verifying Reply Updates**\n\nI'm now implementing updates to the bot reply function, incorporating diagnostic results. I'm focusing on ensuring the bot reply includes detailed diagnostic logs after a timeout. I'm also ensuring the ticket status is updated to \"in_progress\". The integration relies on updating the tickets data with the new bot replies and state changes.\n\n\n**Auditing Clearance Credentials**\n\nI'm now focused on auditing the operational access clearance credentials, and I'm currently setting up the logs for the audit process. I'm focusing on the timing, setting timeouts for each step of the process. I am managing the protocol and its state.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:42:04.173Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"wpfn5ig4","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/portal/support/page.tsx","old_text":"  const handleCreate = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!subject.trim() || !desc.trim()) return;\n\n    const newId = `SLA-TKT-${Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000)}`;\n    const newTkt: ClientSupportTicket = {\n      id: newId,\n      title: subject,\n      status: \"open\",\n      priority,\n      category,\n      projectId: project !== \"none\" ? project : undefined,\n      createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n      desc,\n      replies: []\n    };\n\n    saveTickets([newTkt, ...tickets]);\n    setToastMsg(`Ticket ${newId} initialized on secure network.`);\n    setShowToast(true);\n    setTimeout(() => setShowToast(false), 4000);\n\n    setSelectedTicketId(newId);\n    setSubject(\"\");\n    setDesc(\"\");\n    setProject(\"none\");\n  };\n\n  const handleSendReply = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!replyText.trim() || !selectedTicketId) return;\n\n    const currentReply = replyText;\n    setReplyText(\"\");\n    setIsReplying(true);\n\n    const userReply = {\n      sender: \"Alexander Mercer (Client)\",\n      text: currentReply,\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    const target = tickets.find(t => t.id === selectedTicketId);\n    if (!target) return;\n\n    const updatedReplies = [...(target.replies || []), userReply];\n    const updatedTickets = tickets.map(t => {\n      if (t.id === selectedTicketId) {\n        return { ...t, replies: updatedReplies, status: t.status === \"resolved\" ? \"in_progress\" : t.status };\n      }\n      return t;\n    }) as ClientSupportTicket[];\n\n    saveTickets(updatedTickets);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      let botText = \"Handshake acknowledged. Our on-call systems engineers are reviewing your trace reports inside the secure sandbox.\";\n      let botSender = \"GFF Support Sentinel\";\n\n      if (target.category === \"AI Operations\") {\n        botSender = \"Dr. Sarah Vance (Lead Systems Architect)\";\n        botText = \"Analyzing enclave CPU and HSM logs. The cryptographic state is re-asserted and key rotational interlocks are operating nominally. All propagation latency is mitigated (<0.4ms).\";\n      } else if (target.category === \"Billing\") {\n        botSender = \"Nicolette Durand (Billing & Treasury)\";\n        botText = \"Invoices check completed. Invoice settlement is verified at blockchain epoch block 18290192 under seal 0xDE897FFA.\";\n      } else if (target.category === \"Governance\" || target.category === \"Documents\") {\n        botSender = \"Sovereign Audit Agent\";\n        botText = \"Operator credentials verified at Clearance Level IV. The NIST AI RMF logs are compiled successfully within SGX memory. Access credentials issued.\";\n      }\n\n      const botReply = { sender: botSender, text: botText, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() };\n      \n      saveTickets(updatedTickets.map(t => {\n        if (t.id === selectedTicketId) {\n          return { ...t, replies: [...updatedReplies, botReply], status: \"in_progress\" };\n        }\n        return t;\n      }) as ClientSupportTicket[]);\n      \n      setIsReplying(false);\n    }, 1500);\n  };","new_text":"  const handleCreate = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!subject.trim() || !desc.trim()) return;\n\n    setIsSubmittingForm(true);\n    setSubmittingLogs([\n      \"Negotiating session keys inside Intel SGX memory page...\",\n      \"Binding secure hardware-signed enclave session (Clearance Level III)...\"\n    ]);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setSubmittingLogs(prev => [...prev, \"Encrypting local diagnostics dump payload...\", \"Dispatching secure signal packet to GFF triage array...\"]);\n    }, 600);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      const newId = `SLA-TKT-${Math.floor(1000 + Math.random() * 9000)}`;\n      const newTkt: ClientSupportTicket = {\n        id: newId,\n        title: subject,\n        status: \"open\",\n        priority,\n        category,\n        projectId: project !== \"none\" ? project : undefined,\n        createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n        desc,\n        replies: []\n      };\n\n      saveTickets([newTkt, ...tickets]);\n      setToastMsg(`Sovereign Tunnel ${newId} initialized successfully.`);\n      setShowToast(true);\n      setTimeout(() => setShowToast(false), 4000);\n\n      setSelectedTicketId(newId);\n      setSubject(\"\");\n      setDesc(\"\");\n      setProject(\"none\");\n      setIsSubmittingForm(false);\n      setSubmittingLogs([]);\n    }, 1500);\n  };\n\n  const handleSendReply = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if (!replyText.trim() || !selectedTicketId) return;\n\n    const currentReply = replyText;\n    setReplyText(\"\");\n    setIsReplying(true);\n\n    const userReply = {\n      sender: \"Alexander Mercer (Client)\",\n      text: currentReply,\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    const target = tickets.find(t => t.id === selectedTicketId);\n    if (!target) return;\n\n    const updatedReplies = [...(target.replies || []), userReply];\n    const updatedTickets = tickets.map(t => {\n      if (t.id === selectedTicketId) {\n        return { ...t, replies: updatedReplies, status: t.status === \"resolved\" ? \"in_progress\" : t.status };\n      }\n      return t;\n    }) as ClientSupportTicket[];\n\n    saveTickets(updatedTickets);\n\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      let botText = \"Handshake acknowledged. Our on-call systems engineers are reviewing your trace reports inside the secure sandbox.\";\n      let botSender = \"GFF Support Sentinel\";\n\n      if (target.category === \"AI Operations\") {\n        botSender = \"Dr. Sarah Vance (Lead Systems Architect)\";\n        botText = \"Analyzing enclave CPU and HSM logs. The cryptographic state is re-asserted and key rotational interlocks are operating nominally. All propagation latency is mitigated (<0.4ms).\";\n      } else if (target.category === \"Billing\") {\n        botSender = \"Nicolette Durand (Billing & Treasury)\";\n        botText = \"Invoices check completed. Invoice settlement is verified at blockchain epoch block 18290192 under seal 0xDE897FFA.\";\n      } else if (target.category === \"Governance\" || target.category === \"Documents\") {\n        botSender = \"Sovereign Audit Agent\";\n        botText = \"Operator credentials verified at Clearance Level IV. The NIST AI RMF logs are compiled successfully within SGX memory. Access credentials issued.\";\n      }\n\n      const botReply = { sender: botSender, text: botText, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() };\n      \n      saveTickets(updatedTickets.map(t => {\n        if (t.id === selectedTicketId) {\n          return { ...t, replies: [...updatedReplies, botReply], status: \"in_progress\" };\n        }\n        return t;\n      }) as ClientSupportTicket[]);\n      \n      setIsReplying(false);\n    }, 1500);\n  };\n\n  const runDiagnostic = (idx: number) => {\n    setProtocolRunning(idx);\n    if (idx === 0) {\n      setProtocolLogs([\n        \"[INITIALIZING] Establishing isolated loop communication to SGX Host Node 3...\",\n        \"[COMPILER] Performing memory integrity validation checksum...\"\n      ]);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        setProtocolLogs(prev => [...prev, \"[OK] Found hardware enclave signature (Intel-Xeon-v4)\", \"[OK] Active session keys verified under block 19280.\"]);\n      }, 700);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        setProtocolLogs(prev => [...prev, \"[OK] Attestation signature: 0x98FF...3FAA verified.\", \"[SUCCESS] Secure attestation handshake completed successfully!\"]);\n        setProtocolRunning(null);\n      }, 1600);\n    } else if (idx === 1) {\n      setProtocolLogs([\n        \"[INITIALIZING] Fetching Enclave Page Cache (EPC) allocation metrics...\",\n        \"[ALLOCATOR] Discovering active thread partitions...\"\n      ]);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        setProtocolLogs(prev => [...prev, \"[WARNING] Found 14% thread fragmentation on Node 2\", \"[REALLOCATING] Compacting secure RAM sectors...\"]);\n      }, 700);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        setProtocolLogs(prev => [...prev, \"[OK] Recovered 256MB SGX protected memory cache.\", \"[SUCCESS] EPC memory allocation realigned and optimized!\"]);\n        setProtocolRunning(null);\n      }, 1600);\n    } else {\n      setProtocolLogs([\n        \"[INITIALIZING] Auditing operational access clearance credentials...\",\n        \"[AUDITOR] Compiling NIST AI RMF continuous compliance trails...\"\n      ]);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        setProtocolLogs(prev => [...prev, \"[OK] Integrity trail matched against SGX hardware seal\", \"[ROTATING] Rolling over administration HSM credentials...\"]);\n      }, 700);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        setProtocolLogs(prev => [...prev, \"[OK] Signed key rollover commit block hash: 0xABCD9912\", \"[SUCCESS] Compliant logging structures and HSM keys rotated!\"]);\n        setProtocolRunning(null);\n      }, 1600);\n    }\n  };"}}}
